comments.body:
@bame-da I’ve removed all the other `Helper` templates but this one. We could in principle add a `queryContractKey` function to remove this as well but I’m not sure this is a good idea:

1. For keys, it matters that you fetch within the same transaction since the contents associated with the key can change.
2. We don’t use this anywhere else. I think it’s crucial to actually introduce `fetchByKey` so you have to introduce `fetchByKey` as well as `queryContractId` which just adds more stuff to learn.
